Fleet Financial Group said itsshareholders approved an increase in shares of the company'sauthorized common stock to 100,000,000 shares from 75,000,000shares currently.    The company said shareholders approved the move at theannual meeting in Providence today when the company reportedthat its first quarter earnings rose to 38.5 mln dlrs, or 73cts a share, from 31.7 mln dlrs, or 60 cts a share, in thefirst quarter 1986.    J. Terence Murray, chairman and president of FleetFinancial, said, "Fleet's mortgage banking activities inparticular continued to produce signficant income increases (inthe first quarter)."    Murray said Fleet's mortgage servicing portfolio reached22.1 billion dlrs by March 31, including 1.8 billion dlrspurchased in March. Reuter&#3;